post_text: Celebrate the Fourth safely this year! Find the closest fireworks show for you and your family to catch from your home or from another socially distant spot here.
shared_text:
Bernalillo County NM
July 2 at 9:45 AM ·

This Fourth of July Bernalillo County, in conjunction with the City of Albuquerque, will be hosting four fireworks shows WITHOUT SPECTATORS beginning at 9:20 p.m.
Each site will be closed to the public, but families can enjoy the shows from their homes and other appropriate (and socially distant) locations.
For questions please call (505) 468-7777.
https://www.bernco.gov/community-services/news.aspx?f50e29bf166542cbb6963e258ca152b9blogPostId=bf260039476a4cee9cb70414bd1a8af5#/BlogContent

post_text:
Meet Ms. Emily vanDyck! She's been part of the MAS team since 2015, starting out as an outstanding math teacher. Now, she's in her second year as an instructional coach to help other math teachers get even better. Ms. vanDyck says she likes the extra two weeks of training at the beginning of the school year the most as a teacher at MAS, because of the chances it gives you to keep building your skills.

Want to join our team? Check out our Indeed page to apply for a position that speaks to you here: http://ow.ly/FY4Y50Am3JU

post_text: Today is the 155th anniversary of Juneteenth, the day the Union army arrived in Texas with the good news that the Civil War was over and the slaves there were now free. We hope you take some time to learn about this important holiday and celebrate it with our community today!
shared_text:
Sesame Street
June 19 at 7:00 AM ·

Today is a day of celebration, learning, and sharing traditions and history. We are proud to celebrate #Juneteenth with our Black and African American families, friends, and community.

post_text: Have you met Jennifer Felix? She's our executive assistant by title, but we count on her for all things MAS, from making sure our teachers' licenses are all set to planning events that bring our families together. We couldn't do what we do without her!

post_text:
Our hard-working recruitment specialist Jay is the first friendly face you'll meet at MAS if you join our team. He loves his job and wants you to love yours too! Jay says our school's best selling point is the professional development we offer for teachers. Where many districts only offer a handful of full-day trainings, we dedicate our first three weeks to getting new teachers trained up and keep the momentum going throughout the year with one hour of professional development each morning.

Check out our job postings at http://ow.ly/5Y5850A3iOG. We can't wait to meet you!

post_text: Hey, Bulls! Ready for a summer challenge? Get your art supplies and head outdoors! First, paint a rock with a snazzy design that includes MAS Charter Schools on it. Then take your rock for a walk, run, or bike ride with your friends or family and leave it where other people passing by can appreciate it. Post a picture of it with your location and tag us or include the hashtag #missionachievementandsuccess so we can see it too! Be sure to share any other MAS rocks you see when you’re out on your adventures. Happy trails!

post_text:
Meet Emerald Torres! She was accepted to Central New Mexico Community College, Northern Arizona University, and New Mexico State University, and she's looking forward to starting this fall at Fort Lewis College in Durango, CO to pursue a degree in business management. Baking is her passion, and she hopes to put her degree to work to open a café one day!

Emerald says her determination keeps her on track for success. "I set my mind to my goal. No one else is going to do it for me," she said. "This is what I want, and it's what I strive for." We're so proud of Emerald, both for her acceptance to Fort Lewis and for her entrepreneurial spirit that will take her far. Congratulations, Emerald!

post_text:
**MAS News of the Week**
Happy National School Choice Week, MAS families! We're celebrating our families' ability to choose the right education for their students all week long, starting with an exciting event today at the Albuquerque Convention Center. Join us to hear our students speak about how school choice has changed their lives and their future, and keep an eye out for their writing piece later on!

post_text:
Meet this week's senior, Ivan Gonzalez! Ivan has been accepted to both the University of New Mexico and Central New Mexico Community College. He intends to study mechanical engineering so he can one day work for Sandia National Laboratories or support the US military at Kirtland Air Force Base. He first discovered his ability at a young age. He says his whole family is handy when it comes to cars, and that he realized he was good at it too--and that he enjoyed it!

Ivan says his grandma inspires him to work hard and go far. "She always told me I could do anything," he said, "and I want to make her proud." Congratulations on your acceptance into two great college programs, Ivan! You're making ALL of us proud!
